  <title>Cogl.OnscreenResizeCallback</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function onOnscreenResizeCallback(onscreen: <link xref="Cogl.Onscreen">Cogl.Onscreen</link>, width: Number(gint), height: Number(gint)): void {
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Is a callback type used with the
<link xref="Cogl.Onscreen.add_resize_callback"/> allowing applications to be
notified whenever an <code>onscreen</code> framebuffer is resized.</p>  <p>&lt;note&gt;Cogl automatically updates the viewport of an <code>onscreen</code>
framebuffer that is resized so this callback is also an indication
that the viewport has been modified too&lt;/note&gt;</p>  <p>&lt;note&gt;A resize callback will only ever be called while dispatching
Cogl events from the system mainloop; so for example during
<link xref="Cogl.poll_renderer_dispatch"/>. This is so that callbacks shouldn't
occur while an application might have arbitrary locks held for
example.&lt;/note&gt;</p>
  <p>Since 2.0</p>
